. Trading Philosophy: "Total Confluence"
The strategy does not rely on a single indicator but on a confluence score (0 to 7). For a BUY or SELL signal to be generated, several conditions must align simultaneously:

Trend Structure: Alignment of the EMAs (9, 21, 50, 200).

Higher Timeframe (HTF) Trend: Analysis of the H1 timeframe to ensure trading in the direction of the major flow.

Trend Strength: Use of the ADX indicator to avoid "flat" or ranging markets.

Momentum: RSI (between 45-65 for buys) and MACD (positive and rising histogram).

Price Action: Detection of specific candlestick patterns (Engulfing, Hammers, Shooting Stars).

Volatility & Volume: Squeeze filter (Bollinger vs. Keltner) and volume exceeding its average.
